* Deferred functions

A defer statement schedules a function call to be run just before the function executing the defer returns

The canonical examples are unlocking a mutex or closing a file

	package main

	import (
		"fmt"
		"os"
	)

	func main() {
		fname := "/tmp/file.tmp"
		f, err := os.Open(fname)
		if err != nil {
			fmt.Println(err)
			return
		}
		defer f.Close()

		// do stuff with file
	}



